24/01/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The state secretaries of the foreign affairs ministries of Macedonia, Albania and Croatia met in Skopje Thursday (23 January) to discuss a future accord on joint preparations for NATO membership.Risto Nikovski, Roland Bimo and Zoran Milanovic agreed to hold two more meetings before the document is formally signed in Washington at the end of March.
The three countries hope for a NATO invitation in 2006.
(Utrinski Vesnik - 24/01/03;
MIA, Makfax, A1 TV - 23/01/03)
